metadata.name: A plateful of noodles #229
metadata.description:
This is a grid based collision experiment.

The work is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- space bar : pause/resume animation
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
- s : download canvas as SVG @ current resolution; This can be used with a plotter.

metadata.name: Освобождение #34
metadata.description:
Освобождение (Eng.: Release) is the 3rd part of the current series of my Suprematism, textures and colours study.
This work shows the process of colours leaving their constraining shapes, trying to occupy more area. 

——————

Rendering takes around 30-40 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [Arrow Up / Down] to increase / decrease the drawing speed.
Press [1…6] to change the image resolution up to 10k.
Press [C] after the image is rendered to see 2 different states.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Sep. 2022.

metadata.name: Kings of Babylon #173
metadata.description:
Excavate Kings from the past.
Some are born first, and some are born later.
The long-dead are no longer breathless.
The new kings hail from distant dimensions.
Hunt their crowns, peel their eyes and savor in their glory.

8 Mouths
26 Crowns
12 Eyes

Every Friday for 6 weeks, 2 Kings will be animated and airdropped to the holder, chosen through raffle ritual.
Check @syamarahakim and @spirouzi for the ritual.

metadata.name: COMPUTERS #60
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from pixel array computations and classic noise algorithms.

COMPUTERS is a meditation on the aesthetics of computing in all of its forms. It recalls the types of computation required to build temples, write complex texts, weave detailed textiles, and program computer games. Pixels have always existed in some form or another, before and after the screen. Every iteration of COMPUTERS suggests that computation is both contemporary and ancient.

Press 'p' or click to pause the animation.
Press 's' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: 𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐨𝐧𝐢𝐳𝐞𝐫(𝐨𝐫𝐛𝐬) #22
metadata.description:
"Visual forms are not perceived differently from colors or brightness. They are sense qualities, and the visual character of geometry consists in these sense qualities."

Circles or orbs in clusters! I have been encountering and exploring finely drawn circles at every stage of my life lately. These circles, whether concrete or abstract, are in front of me and they are telling me something, guiding me or putting me in a dead end.

While these circles are sometimes limited to a single circle, sometimes hundreds of them form a team in nested clusters. This occurs with algorithmic randomness. Circle numbers are processed from a very small number frame. sometimes this ratio is high and forms crowded groups.

"As we have already glimpsed and will continue to discover, we are able to expand our awareness beyond the perceived limitations of our own person"

∽∽depending on the screen size you can get different resolutions, which brings out a different side of the project! so you can run this project on all screen sizes and get the output!∽∽

Key:
- Press "s" to export an PNG image


Made with p5.js
Original project by Berke Yapa · Istanbul, 2022

metadata.name: possibleScapes #3
metadata.description:
When memory, photography and code interrelate.

The animated images, accumulations of other images, reveal themselves as fragments of memory.

Like old slides from a time gone by, logs bring possibleScapes that connect differently with each of the spectators.

Working together as a continuous system of gears, the algorithm is associated with the image bank, creating the most diverse interferences, revealing unique possibilities for experimenting with memory.

This is a commemorative token, for the participation of the "savedScapes" project (https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/16116) in the NFT SHOW EUROPE 2022 on the weekend of 17th and 18th September 2022.

As a thank you for all your support, "savedScapes" holders will have the right to mint the same number of editions for free.

The print with all holders will be done tomorrow (September 18th) at 10:00 BRT | 13:00 UTC | 15:00 CEST, and the token will open for collection after one hour at 11:00 am BRT | 14:00 UTC | 16:00 CEST.

Nothing is just one thing.

Generative Token by of Morbeck for fxhash

september 17, 2022
